  "summary": "autotel-devtools 5.1.1: bundled CLI/server contains base64 decoding and network/process keywords requiring human review",
  "details": "The package ships bundled CLI and server entry points (dist/cli.cjs, dist/cli.js, dist/index.cjs, dist/index.js, dist/server/index.cjs, dist/server/index.js, dist/widget.global.js) that contain `Buffer.from(..., 'base64')` decoding plus co-occurring keywords such as `curl`, `ping`, and `POST`. These keyword co-occurrences in minified bundles are commonly produced by legitimate developer-tooling code (HTTP clients, telemetry, build helpers, devtool widgets) but can also indicate exfiltration or dropper behavior. Deeper traced-code corroboration was not available for this version, so intent cannot be determined from the keyword pattern alone. Recommending human review of the bundled entry points to confirm whether the network and base64 primitives belong to documented devtool functionality or to an undisclosed exfiltration / remote-execution path.",
